headline: How Costa Coffee’s Possible Sale at Coca-Cola (KO) Has Changed Its Investment Story
summary: In August 2025, sources reported that The Coca-Cola Company was exploring options for its Costa Coffee business, including a potential sale, in collaboration with investment bank Lazard, following initial discussions with possible buyers. Coca-Cola's CEO previously signaled that Costa had not met internal investment expectations, pointing to broader strategic questions around the company's coffee category ambitions. With a review of Costa Coffee underway, we'll explore how this potential...
